briefdescription.para: Finds intermediate snapshots that have not been committed as the current snapshot.

detaileddescription.para: Transactions can create snapshots that are never the current snapshot because several changes are combined by the transaction into one table metadata update. When each intermediate snapshot is added to table metadata, it is added to the snapshot log, assuming that it will be the current snapshot. When there are multiple snapshot updates, the log must be corrected by suppressing the intermediate snapshot entries.
A snapshot is an intermediate snapshot if it was added but is not the current snapshot.

simplesect.para: A set of snapshot IDs for all added snapshots that were later replaced as the current snapshot in changes

briefdescription.para: Updates the snapshot log by removing intermediate snapshots and handling removed snapshots.
